<!-- page content -->
<div class="right_col" role="main">
  <div class="">
    <div class="page-title">
      <div class="title_left">
        <h3>Connectivity Procedure</h3>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>

    <div class="row">

      <div class="col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
        <div class="x_panel" style="min-height:600px;">
          <div class="x_title">
            <h2>Node Js</h2>
            <div class="clearfix"></div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="x_content">
            <h1 id="gulpfilejs">1. Download SDK</h1>
            <div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissible fade in" role="alert">
              <h2>Download SDK from <code class="buu"><%= link_to 'here', devices_sdks_path(platform: :nodejs), style: 'color: red;' %></code> and unzip it.</h2>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <h1 id="gulpfilejs">2. Install Node and other Dependencies</h1>
            <div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissible fade in" role="alert">
              <h2>Run this command to traverse to the directory.</h2>
              <figure class="br"><pre><code class="but" data-lang="bash"><span class="x">$ </span>cd nodejs</code></pre></figure>
            </div>
            <div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissible fade in" role="alert">
              <h2>Run this command to install nodejs. </h2>
              <figure class="br"><pre><code class="but" data-lang="bash"><span class="x">$ </span>sudo apt-get install nodejs</code></pre></figure>
            </div>
            <div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissible fade in" role="alert">
              <h2>Run this command to install script dependencies.</h2>
              <figure class="br"><pre><code class="but" data-lang="bash"><span class="x">$ </span>npm install aws-iot-device-sdk</code></pre></figure>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <h1 id="gulpfilejs">3. Download Credentials</h1>
            <blockquote>
              <p>Download credentials of your device from owned_devices panel. Unzip this file and copy all the files inside this folder to the certs folder of your current directory. Now, your directory structure should look like this..</p>
            </blockquote>
            <figure class="br"><pre><code class="but" data-lang="bash">nodejs/
├── script.js
└── certs
    ├── private.pem.key
    ├── public.pem.key
    ├── certificate.pem.crt
    └── root-CA.crt</code></pre></figure><hr>
              <h1 id="gulpfilejs">4. Add Device Identity</h1>
              <blockquote>
              <p>Replace <code class="buu">YOUR_DEVICE_SERIAL_NUMBER</code> with the actual serial number of your device which you created on dashboard. You have to replace this variable in the script.js.</p>
            </blockquote>
            <hr>
              <h1 id="gulpfilejs">5. Handle Device Working</h1>
              <blockquote>
              <p>You will get the signal on/off in on_message callback in script.js. Now, control your device as per these signals. Find this at line number 18 in script.js.</p>
            </blockquote>
            </div>
            <hr>
              <h1 id="gulpfilejs">6. Run the script.</h1>
              <div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissible fade in" role="alert">
                <h2>You can run this script using this command.</h2>
                <figure class="br"><pre><code class="but" data-lang="bash"><span class="x">$ </span>node script.js</code></pre></figure>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

